# Project environment

This project requires the CUDA Toolkit, CMake 3.25 or newer, and a host
compiler with C++17 support. Do not assume contributors use a particular OS,
GPU driver, CUDA minor version, or IDE.

## Build conventions

- Both the C++ and CUDA language standards are C++17.
- Default CUDA architectures are `75;80;86;89`. Override them with
  `-DCMAKE_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES=<sm>` for other GPUs.
- Single-configuration generators default to Release. Pass
  `-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug` explicitly for a debug build.
- CMake downloads pinned versions of `nlohmann/json` and GoogleTest through
  `FetchContent`, so the first configure requires network access.
- `blocks/*.cu` is collected with `CONFIGURE_DEPENDS`; adding or removing a
  block automatically triggers CMake reconfiguration.

## Common commands

```bash
cmake -S . -B build && cmake --build build -j
./build/libreisp data/<x>.raw out.png
ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure
./build/tests/isp_tests --gtest_filter='*Perf*'
```

Build outputs are `build/libreisp` and `build/tests/isp_tests`.
